Awesome. We've made
it to features.

00:21:10.936 --> 00:21:14.586 A:middle
And there are a lot of great
new features in tvOS 10.

00:21:15.266 --> 00:21:18.336 A:middle
For those of you who were in
this room before, you heard all

00:21:18.336 --> 00:21:21.276 A:middle
about these directly from
the engineering team.

00:21:21.816 --> 00:21:24.986 A:middle
And don't worry, if you missed
it and came just for design,

00:21:24.986 --> 00:21:26.506 A:middle
first, thank you so much.

00:21:27.636 --> 00:21:29.736 A:middle
And secondly, you
can catch up on

00:21:29.736 --> 00:21:31.956 A:middle
that session on your WWDC app.

00:21:32.746 --> 00:21:34.676 A:middle
So, I'm just going
to be focusing

00:21:34.716 --> 00:21:36.566 A:middle
on the new appearance feature,

00:21:36.616 --> 00:21:39.946 A:middle
because that is what
directly impacts your designs.

00:21:41.896 --> 00:21:46.846 A:middle
There is now light and dark
appearance on the Apple TV.

00:21:46.846 --> 00:21:49.896 A:middle
And this is user
specified in settings.

00:21:49.896 --> 00:21:52.556 A:middle
And it changes the look
of the entire system.

00:21:53.366 --> 00:21:55.766 A:middle
Pretty much every single
control has been adjusted

00:21:55.766 --> 00:21:57.906 A:middle
to some degree for
dark appearance.

00:21:58.456 --> 00:22:00.266 A:middle
This include place
holder images,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:21:58.456 --> 00:22:00.266 A:middle
This include place
holder images,

00:22:00.266 --> 00:22:01.876 A:middle
they're dark instead of light.

00:22:02.266 --> 00:22:03.696 A:middle
Shadows have different values.

00:22:04.176 --> 00:22:06.486 A:middle
And this is a great
new feature on tvOS.

00:22:07.916 --> 00:22:12.276 A:middle
So, to support dark appearance,
your app needs to opt in.

00:22:12.886 --> 00:22:15.146 A:middle
And I encourage you to do
so, because you've seen

00:22:15.146 --> 00:22:17.976 A:middle
in this talk today
how awesome it is.

00:22:18.746 --> 00:22:23.296 A:middle
So, opt in and your app will
respect people's preferences

00:22:23.296 --> 00:22:25.466 A:middle
on how they wish to
experience their TV

00:22:25.826 --> 00:22:27.086 A:middle
in their own environment.

00:22:28.696 --> 00:22:32.576 A:middle
Now, user preferences also
apply to accessibility.

00:22:33.456 --> 00:22:37.486 A:middle
And Apple TV is packed full
of accessibility features

00:22:37.486 --> 00:22:40.266 A:middle
that provide the best user
experience for everyone.

00:22:41.606 --> 00:22:45.276 A:middle
Apps implementing custom fonts
should match the accessibility

00:22:45.276 --> 00:22:49.176 A:middle
behavior of system fonts and
respect settings like bold type.

00:22:50.286 --> 00:22:53.056 A:middle
Accessibility options
also can change contrast,

00:22:53.346 --> 00:22:55.166 A:middle
reduce motion, and more.

00:22:55.796 --> 00:22:57.566 A:middle
So, if you have a
UIKit based app

00:22:58.766 --> 00:23:01.336 A:middle
that could be made accessible
for very little effort.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:22:58.766 --> 00:23:01.336 A:middle
that could be made accessible
for very little effort.

00:23:01.806 --> 00:23:04.576 A:middle
So, I encourage you to check out
these sessions to learn more.

00:23:07.696 --> 00:23:11.646 A:middle
So, appearance and accessibility
features are powerful

00:23:11.646 --> 00:23:12.746 A:middle
on tvOS 10.

00:23:13.236 --> 00:23:16.016 A:middle
And I'm looking forward to
seeing your apps support them.

