00:24:04.976 --> 00:24:07.076 A:middle
And with one click
from the main screen,

00:24:07.506 --> 00:24:09.006 A:middle
you're instantly into a workout.

00:24:10.216 --> 00:24:10.746 A:middle
That's it.

00:24:11.386 --> 00:24:13.126 A:middle
Main screen to workout.

00:24:13.726 --> 00:24:14.716 A:middle
It's that easy.

00:24:14.716 --> 00:24:17.376 A:middle
And it's not overwhelming,
which is great,

00:24:17.466 --> 00:24:19.806 A:middle
because you don't want
any additional barriers

00:24:19.806 --> 00:24:22.846 A:middle
between you and getting fit.

00:24:23.056 --> 00:24:25.136 A:middle
Zova does a great job
with their layout,

00:24:25.386 --> 00:24:28.086 A:middle
because they use large graphics,
and it keeps you focused

00:24:28.086 --> 00:24:29.926 A:middle
on the content of the app.

00:24:30.776 --> 00:24:33.486 A:middle
This app also does something
that is really great.

00:24:34.006 --> 00:24:38.706 A:middle
If you put Zova in the top shelf
of your Apple TV, you'll be able

00:24:38.706 --> 00:24:40.916 A:middle
to jump immediately
into a workout,

00:24:41.226 --> 00:24:44.096 A:middle
because it uses dynamic
content in the top shelf.

00:24:44.966 --> 00:24:46.836 A:middle
If you want to find
out more about it,

00:24:46.836 --> 00:24:50.486 A:middle
I will link to the Apple TV Tech
Talks and the resources today.

00:24:50.486 --> 00:24:52.906 A:middle
So, that is Zova.

00:24:53.806 --> 00:25:00.206 A:middle
This next app that I want to
show you is called, Reuters TV.


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:24:53.806 --> 00:25:00.206 A:middle
This next app that I want to
show you is called, Reuters TV.

00:25:01.156 --> 00:25:04.756 A:middle
And Reuters really
reimagined what news could be

00:25:05.026 --> 00:25:06.066 A:middle
on the Apple TV.

00:25:07.156 --> 00:25:09.746 A:middle
If you think about traditional
news, when you turn it

00:25:09.746 --> 00:25:12.926 A:middle
on you may be popping in five
minutes late to a broadcast

00:25:12.926 --> 00:25:15.546 A:middle
and you've already missed all of
the big news stories of the day.

00:25:16.506 --> 00:25:19.076 A:middle
And I know you can
definitely get all your news

00:25:19.076 --> 00:25:21.696 A:middle
from the internet, but
if you really wanted

00:25:21.696 --> 00:25:26.026 A:middle
to just watch a nice segment
that had everything you needed

00:25:26.026 --> 00:25:28.966 A:middle
to know, well, wouldn't
that be great?

00:25:30.116 --> 00:25:31.996 A:middle
Well, that's exactly
what Reuters did.

00:25:32.836 --> 00:25:36.996 A:middle
When you open this app you
only have one decision to make.

00:25:37.806 --> 00:25:41.286 A:middle
And that is, how much time do
you have for the news today?

00:25:42.446 --> 00:25:44.086 A:middle
You make a single action.

00:25:44.426 --> 00:25:47.726 A:middle
You choose whether that's
10, 15, or 30 minutes.

00:25:47.726 --> 00:25:49.376 A:middle
And as soon as you select one,

00:25:49.816 --> 00:25:52.026 A:middle
you are immediately
into the experience.

00:25:53.146 --> 00:25:55.296 A:middle
You're given a quick
trailer of what videos are

00:25:55.296 --> 00:25:58.326 A:middle
in your playlist, and then
you're watching the news.

00:25:59.916 --> 00:26:02.496 A:middle
If you wanted to swipe up
to reveal that playlist,


WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:181083,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:25:59.916 --> 00:26:02.496 A:middle
If you wanted to swipe up
to reveal that playlist,

00:26:02.496 --> 00:26:04.746 A:middle
you can jump to stories that
you are more interested in.

00:26:05.566 --> 00:26:09.346 A:middle
And that's the beauty of
next level on demand content.

00:26:10.166 --> 00:26:13.156 A:middle
Not only did I choose when
I wanted to watch this,

00:26:13.656 --> 00:26:15.486 A:middle
but I was also easily
able to skip

00:26:15.566 --> 00:26:17.716 A:middle
to what I wanted
to watch with ease.

00:26:18.846 --> 00:26:21.496 A:middle
This app makes it possible
to watch the news again.

00:26:23.216 --> 00:26:27.256 A:middle
Now, while there's an amazing
team who's behind providing all

00:26:27.256 --> 00:26:31.956 A:middle
of this news content, the apps
focused experience is what truly

00:26:31.956 --> 00:26:32.676 A:middle
makes it great.

00:26:32.796 --> 00:26:33.466 A:middle
All right.

00:26:34.536 --> 00:26:37.106 A:middle
So, that is Reuters TV.

00:26:37.646 --> 00:26:40.246 A:middle
Next up is a game.

00:26:40.246 --> 00:26:43.986 A:middle
And this game is
called, Chameleon Run.

